COMMERCIAL WEBGLIMPSE MODULES v 2.0.11

REQUIRES: Webglimpse v2.0.5 or above.  

If you have downloaded these modules separately from the main Webglimpse 
package, first copy all the .pm files to the /lib subdirectory of the
webglimpse home directory.

	cp  *.pm   WEBGLIMPSE_HOME/lib

where WEBGLIMPSE_HOME is the directory you have installed webglimpse, such as
/usr/local/webglimpse.

Second, copy the wg* files to the /dist subdirectory of the webglimpse home 
directory.

	cp  wg*   WEBGLIMPSE_HOME/dist

Lastly, either click the 'Save Changes' button using the webministration interface for each archive, or copy the wg* files manually:

	cp  wgfields  YOUR_ARCHIVE_DIR/.wgfields
	cp  wgoutput.cfg  YOUR_ARCHIVE_DIR/.wgoutput.cfg

Note the initial "."   Then edit .wgoutput.cfg and .wgfields as needed to customize
your results output.  See

	http://webglimpse.net/docs/howto_customizeoutput.html

for more details.

It is not necessary to rebuild your archives when adding the commercial modules; but 
if you also upgraded all of Webglimpse at the same time, then you should rebuild.

Send questions, comments, suggestions, fixes to gvelez@iwhome.com.


